    <p>
        The surface area of a sphere is <m>{\color{blue} 4 \pi r^2}</m>
    </p>
    <example>
        <statement>
            <p>
                Find the surface area of a sphere whose
                diameter is <m>21 \, \text{cm}</m>.
            </p>
        </statement>
        <solution>
            <p>
                The diameter of the sphere is <m>21 \, \text{cm}</m>, so the radius <m>r = \frac{21}{2} = 10.5</m> cm.

                
                

                
            </p>
            <p>
                The formula for the surface area of a sphere is:
            </p>
            <p>
                <m>\text{SA}= 4 \pi \text{r}^2</m>
            </p>
            <p>
                <md>
                    
                    <mrow>\text{SA}= \amp 4 \times \frac{22}{7} \times 10.5^2 </mrow>
                    <mrow>= \amp 4 \times \frac{22}{7} \times 110.25 </mrow>
                   
                    <mrow>= \amp 4 \times 346.5 </mrow>
                    <mrow>= \amp 1386 \text{ cm}^2 </mrow>
                </md>
            </p>
            <p>
                Therefore, the surface area of the sphere is <m>{\color{blue}1386 \text{ cm}^2}</m>.
            </p>
        </solution>
    </example>
    <example>
        <statement>
            <p>
                Find the area of the figure below. Use <m>\pi =3.142</m>
            </p>
            <image width="50%">
            <latex-image label="sphere-3">
                \begin{tikzpicture}[scale=0.4]
                    
                    % Outer circle representing the sphere
                    \draw[very thick] (0,0) circle(10);

                    % Equator (ellipse to show 3D)
                    \draw[very thick,dashed] (-10,0) arc (180:360:10 and 2.5); % front half
                    \draw[very thick,dashed, opacity=0.3] (10,0) arc (0:180:10 and 2.5); % back half (hidden)

                    % Radius lin8
                    \draw[red, thick] (0,0) -- (0,-10);
                    \node[red] at (3.5,-4.5) {\huge{21 m}};

                    % Center dot
                    \fill[very thick] (0,0) circle (6pt);
                \end{tikzpicture}
            </latex-image>
            </image>
        </statement>
        <solution>
            <p>
                The radius of the sphere is <m>21\, \text{m}</m>.

                

                
              

                
            </p>
            <p>
                The formula for the surface area of a sphere is:
                <m>\text{SA} = 4 \pi r^2</m>
            </p>
            <p>
                Substituting the values:
            </p>
            <p>
                  <md>
                    <mrow>\text{SA} = \amp 4 \times 3.142 \times 21^2</mrow>
                    <mrow>= \amp 4 \times 3.142 \times 441</mrow>
                    <mrow>= \amp 4 \times 1385.622</mrow>
                    <mrow>= \amp 5542.488 \text{ m}^2</mrow>
                </md>
            </p>
            <p>
                Therefore, the surface area of the sphere is <m>{\color{blue}5542.49 \text{ m}^2}</m>.
            </p>
        </solution>
